From 8dab4dd962f1e464ec8de8ef98e5e7886dcb53ac Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dev <dev@example.com>
Date: Tue, 30 Jun 2026 16:53:39 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] Wire per-job heartbeat: WatchJob.lastHeartbeat tracked by
 FileWatcherService and surfaced in JobTablePanel

- WatchJob gains a lastHeartbeat field, distinct from lastTransfer, with
  getter/setter. Pushed over the same WatchJob WebSocket payload that
  already carries job state (JOB_STATE / INIT), so no new wire DTO needed.
- FileWatcherService schedules a per-job heartbeat tick (via the existing
  Scheduler, keyed jobId:heartbeat) on startJob(), cancelled on stopJob().
  Interval follows AppConfig.heartbeatIntervalSeconds (falls back to 30s
  if that's 0/disabled), so it's independent of each watcher's own
  mechanism (NIO loop, polling, or blocking remote exec) and ticks even
  for connection types with no natural per-event tick of their own.
  touchHeartbeat() is a no-op once a job goes IDLE, so a stopped job
  stops reporting liveness instead of looking falsely alive.
  recordSuccess()/markTransferring() also stamp lastHeartbeat so the UI
  reflects real activity immediately rather than waiting for the next
  scheduled tick.
- JobTablePanel now renders a real 'Last Heartbeat' column backed by
  WatchJob.getLastHeartbeat(), alongside the existing 'Last Transfer'
  column, instead of one column standing in for both.
---
